      },
      {
        "step_no": 2,
        "text": "Heat oil in a large heavy-bottomed pot over medium heat until shimmering. Add diced onion, carrots, and celery and sauté, stirring occasionally, until softened and translucent.",
        "time_min": 8
      },
      {
        "step_no": 3,
        "text": "Add minced garlic, ground cumin, smoked paprika, and optional red pepper flakes; cook, stirring, until aromatic but not burned.",
        "time_min": 1
      },
      {
        "step_no": 4,
        "text": "Stir in tomato paste and cook for a minute to deepen its flavor, then add crushed tomatoes and stir to combine.",
        "time_min": 2
      },
      {
        "step_no": 5,
        "text": "Add rinsed lentils, vegetable broth, bay leaf, salt, and pepper. Bring the pot to a gentle boil over medium-high heat.",
        "time_min": 5
      },
      {
        "step_no": 6,
        "text": "Reduce heat to low, partially cover the pot, and simmer gently until lentils are tender but hold their shape, stirring occasionally to prevent sticking.",
        "time_min": 25
      },
      {
        "step_no": 7,
        "text": "Remove the bay leaf, stir in the chopped greens and simmer uncovered until the greens are wilted and incorporated, then adjust seasoning with salt and pepper and stir in lemon juice.",
        "time_min": 3
      },
      {
